channel.title: [Showoff/Might Release] Origin of Nightmares [Showoff/Might Release]
channel.description:
Well, my last model...sucked in most peoples opinions...and mine too :S. I'm hoping to prove to you guys that C4D was not a step back for me. Im getting past the artists block, i hope. Please leave comments, as i need to know how to improve with c4d...Please and thank you.
EDIT::: Pictures are large again...(Sorry...) trying to get a size that works, just click on the image if you are too lazy to scroll over to see the rest of it, i know i am :D
ALSO --- You may or may not have seem/remember my hi-poly metaseq model, Harvester of Nightmares, [s]here is the link to a pic of it[/s],...Couldnt get a link to work, heres a thumbnail [URL=http://img251.imageshack.us/i/harvesterofnightmares.png/][IMG]http://img251.imageshack.us/img251/2339/harvesterofnightmares.th.png[/img][/URL] ... I was thinking of making a 'nightmare' weapon set and fit them into RSPS, tell me your thoughts on this. ~~~~~~~~~~~Pictures~~~~~~~~~~ [URL=http://img59.imageshack.us/i/aprogress.jpg/][IMG]http://img59.imageshack.us/img59/2748/aprogress.jpg[/img][/URL]
[URL=http://img130.imageshack.us/i/aprogress2.jpg/][IMG]http://img130.imageshack.us/img130/9457/aprogress2.jpg[/img][/URL]
[URL=http://img408.imageshack.us/i/aprogress3.jpg/][IMG]http://img408.imageshack.us/img408/773/aprogress3.jpg[/img][/URL]
[URL=http://img20.imageshack.us/i/aprogress4.jpg/][IMG]http://img20.imageshack.us/img20/8097/aprogress4.jpg[/img][/URL]
[URL=http://img716.imageshack.us/i/aprogress5.jpg/][IMG]http://img716.imageshack.us/img716/1325/aprogress5.jpg[/img][/URL]
[URL=http://img39.imageshack.us/i/aprogressinfo.png/][IMG]http://img39.imageshack.us/img39/7705/aprogressinfo.png[/img][/URL] ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~ LASTLY: Soon I will be releasing a big pack of all the blades of weapons i have made. Just the blade part, no hilts or fancy stuff on them. They will be in metaseq form, therefore a big .mqo

item.dc:creator: @Tribbinator Tribbinator
item.description:
@Tribbinator wrote:

@everyone…Thanks for all the feedback, you guys are great!

@Dylan…I admit, im a poly killer. The weird thing is, i didnt even intend to make the color transition using all those polys. i just subdivided a cube to have like 25 sections, and modelled it. Coloring for me is a whole different story…i will have a blank white model before i color it, is that odd?

item.dc:creator: @dylan_0789 dylan_0789
item.description:
@dylan_0789 wrote:

Definately overkill on poly. Think of it ingame: 70% of those faces wouldnt be noticed, and 70% of the color blend wouldnt be noticed. If you could figure out how to produce the same quality using less faces you’re skills in modeling will improve to a further extent quicker.
